  {
    question: 'When do I receive my TFR (severance pay)?',
    answer: 'If your TFR is kept with your employer, you receive the full accumulated amount when your employment relationship ends, regardless of the reason -- resignation, dismissal, mutual agreement, retirement, or end of a fixed-term contract. There is no minimum service period. Even if you leave after a few months, you are entitled to the TFR accrued during that time. The employer must pay it with your final payslip (ultima busta paga), typically within 30-45 days of the employment end date. If your TFR is allocated to a pension fund (fondo pensione), you will access it according to the fund\'s rules, generally at retirement.',
