    question: 'Can I transfer my TFR to a pension fund after the initial 6-month choice period?',
    answer: 'Yes, you can switch your TFR allocation from the employer to a pension fund (fondo pensione) <strong>at any time after the initial 6-month period</strong>. However, this choice is <strong>irreversible</strong>: once you redirect future TFR accruals to a pension fund, you cannot switch back to keeping them with the employer. The TFR already accumulated with the employer before the switch remains with the employer (it is not transferred to the pension fund) and will be paid out when your employment ends. Only <em>future</em> TFR accruals from the date of the switch onward will flow to the pension fund. To make the switch, you submit a specific form (modulo di adesione) to your employer indicating your chosen pension fund. The change takes effect from the month following your request. This flexibility is governed by Art. 8 of D.Lgs. 252/2005 (see <a href="https://www.normattiva.it/uri-res/N2Ls?urn:nir:stato:decreto.legislativo:2005-12-05;252" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Normattiva &mdash; D.Lgs. 252/2005</a>).',
